Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] This evening, President Franjo Tudjman received 
Internal Affairs Minister Ivan Jarnjak, together with his aides. 
Following the meeting a statement was issued outlining personnel 
changes in the Internal Affairs Ministry of the Republic of 
Croatia. 
  Under a presidential decree, Zlatko Gledec was appointed 
deputy internal affairs minister; Mladen Lackovic was appointed 
assistant internal affairs minister responsible for information 
and personnel; Zellko Tomljenovic, the outgoing deputy minister 
of internal affairs of the Republic of Croatia, was appointed 
ministerial adviser. 

